This article is a statement made by President Obama on August 26, 2009, regarding the death of Senator Ted Kennedy. The President expresses his sadness and describes Kennedy as a dear friend who played a significant role in advancing civil rights, healthcare, and the economy through his legislative efforts. The President values Kennedy's counsel and support, both during his time in the Senate and his presidential campaign. Despite battling a serious illness, Kennedy continued to provide encouragement and wisdom to the President. The President acknowledges that an important chapter in history has ended with Kennedy's passing and describes him as the greatest United States Senator of their time. The President also extends his condolences to Kennedy's family, recognizing him as their patriarch and a source of strength and support.